<p>In an angular service, we're exposing a function which provides a token and should be blocking, until the token is loaded.</p>  <p>the critical part in the service</p>  <pre><code>....     function getToken(){         tokenPromise().then(             function(token){ return token;},             function(error){ return null;}     } .... </code></pre>  <p><strong>How do I turn this to a blocking function code?</strong></p>  <p>so that <code>service.getToken();</code> is blocking/synchronious until token is there.</p>  <p>Returning a promise/callback is not a solution.</p>